## 2. Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `cargo build --release` produces a single binary
- [ ] `cargo test` is green
- [ ] `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` is clean
- [ ] `cargo fmt --check` is clean
- [ ] `--help` prints the documented command surface
- [ ] Exit codes are stable + documented (POSIX convention: 0 ok, non-zero error)

## 3. Non-goals

- No GUI — terminal output only
- No background services — exec-and-exit
- No async runtime unless I/O fan-out demands it (single-threaded by default)

